'''Alexander Abreu Manresa''' (September 6, 1976) is a Cuban [[trumpet player]], songwriter and singer. He leads the band [[Havana D'Primera]].{{Citation needed|date=September 2024}}

He was born in [[Cienfuegos]] on September 6, 1976. By the age of 20, he had become a widely recognized Cuban musician after graduating from the [[National Art Schools (Cuba)]] (ENA) of [[Havana]] in 1994. He went on to be a trumpet teacher at ENA and professor of [[jazz]] and [[Cuban music]] at the [[Rhythmic Music Conservatory]] of [[Copenhagen]] in Denmark.{{Cita requerida|date=September 2024}}

In 2012, he appeared as an actor in the film [[7 Days in Havana]], in the segment "Tuesday Jam Session" with [[Emir Kusturica]].
